          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-08-18 17:08:14" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the taste of wormwood, a bitter-tasting herb used as a cure for intestinal worms. Compare {D:3.21}.</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>bitter</Gloss>
                <Gloss>bitter like wormwood</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>As already noted in {D:3.21}, the meaning of {L:ἄψινθος&lt;SDBG:ἄψινθος:000000&gt;} in {S:06600801100032} is not that the waters turned into a particular plant but that the waters came to be as bitter as the plant in question.</Comments>
